  "body": "Some block synchronization is very slow, sometimes takes 10 minute only one block.\nIf you check the gist, you can see the secund and third 'imported' log with a huge different.\nAfter the first syncing process the geth has worked ~2 days good.\nOn 22. 9. has anything started and the block sync has slowed down so much, that the geth have put himself to 'syncing' status until i shut him down.\nToday ( 23. 9. ) have realized the problem, and I have connected to the console and have checked the eth.syncing command:\n\n```\n{\n  currentBlock: 2306923,\n  highestBlock: 2311008,\n  knownStates: 0,\n  pulledStates: 0,\n  startingBlock: 2306818\n}\n```\n\nGeth has fell behind with many block during syncing. Then i have applied 'debug.vmodule(\"downloader=6\")' command and created a GIST with the shorted log:\nhttps://gist.github.com/iFA88/3b4ffa9e15c16c34c000d8c5f2bf4f26\n\nI use Geth/v1.5.0-unstable-c8d6efd6/linux/go1.7 on debian Jessie.\n",
